# Error handling

- **Nest:** Use Nest HTTP exceptions (`BadRequestException`, `InternalServerErrorException`, `HttpException`). Global filter preserves object bodies for special cases (e.g. HTTP 418 teapot payload).
- **Never** leak stack traces in JSON responses for expected demo scenarios; log details with pino / Sentry instead.
- **Frontend:** Surface API errors via toast; refetch run history on settled mutation so failed runs still appear when the backend persisted them.
